    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="366"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 102.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 4, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 17th ultimo, No. 59,
                    together with its accompanying memorandum of a conversation that you had with
                    Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys, upon the subject of the forcible surrender, by General
                    Mejia, of refugees from the insurgent army to the armed enemies of the United
                    States, has been received, and your proceedings are approved.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
